---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Cost Receipts - SqueezyAgent"
  description="Draft cost receipt docs for SqueezyAgent."
  activeDoc="/docs/cost-receipts/"
  heading="Cost receipts"
  lead="Receipts make context spend visible: what was read, what was sent, what changed, and what was avoided."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <span class="status-pill">draft</span>
    <h2>What a receipt should track</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Code slices</h3>
        <p>Path, content hash, byte range, line range, freshness, and reason.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Tool output</h3>
        <p>Bytes scanned, preview size, spill handle, and model-facing tokens.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Repeated reads</h3>
        <p>Unchanged ranges should return compact receipt references.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Benchmarks</h3>
        <p>Receipts become the evidence behind any public savings claim.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Implemented foundation</h2>
    <p>
      Current fallback tools already return cost hints, output caps, sha256
      receipts, spill handles for large outputs, and aggregate result budgets.
      Receipt-backed read stubs and structure-aware navigation are later
      structural savings.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Concrete tool behaviors</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Search modes</h3>
        <p>`grep` can return content, files-with-matches, or counts depending on how much context the model actually needs.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Spill handles</h3>
        <p>Large reads and tool outputs become compact previews plus local handles for exact follow-up ranges.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Aggregate budget</h3>
        <p>Parallel tool results are packed against one model-facing budget for the whole round.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Stable tool surface</h3>
        <p>Tool schemas are sorted deterministically to keep provider prompt/cache prefixes stable.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
